eu.opends.analyzer

Class DataUnit

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.opends.analyzer.DataUnit
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class DataUnit
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Data object containing position and speed of the car, as well as the current date. Based on AnalyzationData.java from the CARS-project.
    Author:
    Marco Mueller, Rafael Math
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • DataUnit

        public DataUnit(java.util.Date date,
                float xpos,
                float ypos,
                float zpos,
                float xrot,
                float yrot,
                float zrot,
                float wrot,
                float speed,
                float steeringWheelPos,
                float gasPedalPos,
                float brakePedalPos,
                boolean isEngineOn,
                com.jme3.math.Quaternion oculusRiftOrientation)
        Parameters:
        date - The date, when the data set was taken.
        xpos - The position of the car on the x axis.
        ypos - The position of the car on the y axis.
        zpos - The position of the car on the z axis.
        xrot - The rotation of the car (x component of quaternion)
        yrot - The rotation of the car (y component of quaternion)
        zrot - The rotation of the car (z component of quaternion)
        wrot - The rotation of the car (w component of quaternion)
        speed - The current speed of the car in kilometers per hour.
        steeringWheelPos - The position of the steering wheel: -1 full left, 0 centered, 1 full right.
        gasPedalPos - The position of the gas pedal: 0 no acceleration, 1 full acceleration
        brakePedalPos - The position of the brake pedal: -1 full break/negative acceleration, 0 no acceleration
        isEngineOn - Engine state
        oculusRiftOrientation - Head orientation (when using Oculus Rift)

        speed - The current speed of the car in kilometers per hour.
        steeringWheelPos - The position of the steering wheel: -1 full left, 0 centered, 1 full right.
        gasPedalPos - The position of the gas pedal: 0 no acceleration, 1 full acceleration
        brakePedalPos - The position of the brake pedal: -1 full break/negative acceleration, 0 no acceleration
        isEngineOn - Engine state
        traveledDistance - traveled distance
